We'll surprise him. Come on.

239
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:53,040
- You comin' or what?
- I'm comin'.

240
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:20,200
I don't think
we should go up there, Leroy.

241
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:22,720
Oh, that's fine, girlfriend.

242
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:25,960
I tell you what. You stay down here,
and you keep an eye out.

243
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:28,880
You think you can do that?

244
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:34,120
Yeah, I can do that.

245
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:46,440
Man, there's enough room
for ten families in here.

246
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:49,280
Spenser!
Spenser, are you up here?

247
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,840
Spenser!

248
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:17,160
Spenser, you back in there?

249
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:21,160
I ain't stupid.

250
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:30,000
"Or maybe you're just
too chickenshit for this kinda work. "

251
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:53,360
- Fool.

252
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:00,600
Spenser?

253
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:00,880
Spenser?

254
00:25:01,120 --> 00:25:04,680
How can you say that of me?
I've never been unfaithful to you.

255
00:25:05,320 --> 00:25:08,240
I'm not talking
about another woman, John.

256
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:11,640
- What's that supposed to mean?
- connect the dots, John.

257
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:15,720
Everyone else has. Ever since Paris.
Ever since Cybill killed herself

258
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:18,800
Cybill's death
was a sailing accident.

259
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:23,320
- That's what I am - a survivor.
- Tiffany!

260
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:28,800
I'm sorry, John. Sorry for the both of us.
Sorry for the child that... we never had.

261
00:25:29,640 --> 00:25:32,240
- And never will!
- Tiffany, don't get...

262
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:39,560
Now the anti-aircraft battery!
They're firing.

263
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,640
- Where?
- I think it's the barracks.

264
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:44,480
They're over by the barracks.

265
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:49,000
We can hear the staccato firing, and now
here it comes. Baghdad is lighting up!

266
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:54,280
Tracers flaring up like... like
angry hornets from every rooftop now.

267
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:58,400
We cannot see the bombers, but the fire
of their munitions is shaking the city.

268
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:02,320
It's shaking our hotel. Oh, look! See it?

269
00:26:03,080 --> 00:26:05,760
There! Right over there,
flying just over the rooftops.

270
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:08,000
Spenser, you back in there?

271
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:17,360
No!

272
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:37,400
Spenser!

273
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:13,400
You can't do that,
you miserable stinkin' thing!

274
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,800
Come on, Spense.
I'm gonna get you outta here.

275
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:32,640
Man... this ain't right.

276
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:46,400
Who are you?

277
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,280
Leroy, we gotta get outta this place!

278
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:01,880
Hello? Miss?

279
00:29:28,280 --> 00:29:30,200
Leroy. Leroy!

280
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:42,960
Leroy?

281
00:29:55,080 --> 00:29:56,560
- Leroy?
- Jesus!

282
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:59,400
- You scared the shit outta me.
- I thought you were dead!

283
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:02,440
- You was just layin' there.
- A man ain't dead...

284
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:04,600
..just cos he's layin' on the floor.

285
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:07,160
I was listenin'. Something's in there.

286
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:11,280
As a matter of fact, why don't you
crawl in there and see what it is?

287
00:30:12,080 --> 00:30:15,000
Turkey-brain! Are you hittin' on me
like I'm here to save your ass?

288
00:30:15,360 --> 00:30:18,280
You're gonna stick your dumb head
in there and lose it, like Spenser!

289
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:21,760
- What kinda shit you talkin'?
- I'm talkin' we gotta get outta here.

290
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:25,360
The x-ray lady's back.
She's out back right now by the van.

291
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:27,840
She got a man with her
the size of Detroit!

292
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:29,680
Damn. You seen Spenser?

293
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:32,640
- I seen Spenser all right.
- He find anything?

294
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:35,720
Somethin' found him. He's dead, Leroy.

295
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:39,040
I think scared to death.

296
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:42,520
- You sure?
- You thought he was white before?

297
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:45,120
You should see that sucker now!

298
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:58,640
There is somebody in there.
The door's been pried.

299
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:01,480
- I told you there'd be another one.
- Out the front.

300
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:06,320
Wah!

301
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:09,320
Oh, shit!

302
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:11,360
Oh, my hand!

303
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:17,600
Pry it open at the bottom,
enough so Prince can get in.

304
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:28,680
- Come on, Fool!
- Agh! What are you doin'?

305
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:31,840
Stay here in the open
so the fuckin' dog can see you.

306
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:34,600
You think I'm crazy? He's got teeth
he ain't even used yet!

307
00:31:35,320 --> 00:31:37,920
Do like I say,
or I'm gonna take your head off.

308
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:43,360
I'm gonna nail that sucker, don't worry.

309
00:31:43,840 --> 00:31:46,120
- I'm worryin'.

310
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:47,400
Kill him!

311
00:31:55,520 --> 00:31:56,800
Uh-oh.

312
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:01,520
- Where'd he go?

313
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:03,640
Shit!

314
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:15,800
- Leroy!
- What the hell are you doin', Fool?!

315
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:17,720
Come on!

316
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:30,840
I'm gonna take your fuckin' head off!

317
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:40,880
I heard him yell!
I heard him go down!

318
00:32:46,160 --> 00:32:49,200
- I told you, don't mess with me.
- Man, that saved your body.

319
00:32:49,520 --> 00:32:51,640
- Are these people crazy or what?
- You ask 'em!

320
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:54,200
Get in there, Daddy!
Get in there and get 'em!

321
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:56,120
Make it safe for Mommy!

322
00:33:19,880 --> 00:33:21,800
Ow! Damn!

323
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:29,920
Little doggy baby! Someone is in here.

324
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:33,400
The people under the stairs
got the so-called gasman.

325
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:37,760
- The other one must be upstairs.
- Princey... Daddy'll get him.

326
00:33:38,920 --> 00:33:42,920
That's a big-caliber automatic.
Did you ever see the holes they tear?

327
00:33:43,680 --> 00:33:47,280
- We can hide under the bed.
- I ain't goin' in there, man.

328
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:50,680
No room. Find your own.

329
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:36,720
Aha!

330
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:43,600
Run, Fool!

331
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:52,960
Fool... Yee-ha!

332
00:34:54,240 --> 00:34:56,120
Got him!

333
00:34:57,840 --> 00:34:59,560
Oh, Daddy!

334
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:04,600
- See that? He came at me like a bull.
- Just like a bull!

335
00:35:05,080 --> 00:35:07,160
A big one!

336
00:35:07,520 --> 00:35:09,720
- Did you hear what he called me?
- He called you a fool.

337
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:11,440
He's the fool!

338
00:35:12,200 --> 00:35:14,440
The only good fool's a dead one.

339
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:24,080
- Upstairs might be a mess.
- I don't want a mess. I better go look.

340
00:35:24,640 --> 00:35:26,760
We might have to mop up a little.

341
00:35:41,440 --> 00:35:43,920
Thought I heard something. Stay there.

342
00:36:31,560 --> 00:36:34,360
Get back in the cellar, you little bastard.

343
00:36:41,560 --> 00:36:46,080
You little animal shit!
I get the dog up here, you'll be sorry.

344
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:27,320
My... my name is Fool.

345
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,880
- What's yours?
- Alice.

346
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:35,960
Don't be scared. You...
you never seen a brother before?

347
00:37:36,240 --> 00:37:38,760
- I never had a brother.
- No, I mean a black dude.

348
00:37:39,880 --> 00:37:41,800
There's black folks
in the neighborhood.

349
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:44,160
Neighborhood?

350
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:47,400
The neighborhood.

351
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:49,440
You know, outside?

352
00:37:50,520 --> 00:37:52,680
Well, that's outside, not in here.

353
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:55,440
So you get outside, don't you?

354
00:37:58,000 --> 00:38:01,480
- Are... are you sayin' never?
- Can't get out. No one ever has.

355
00:38:02,640 --> 00:38:05,120
Well... well, I'm gonna get out.

356
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:07,840
I'm a whole other thing.

357
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:12,640
People have tried.

358
00:38:14,840 --> 00:38:17,320
You... you mean
the... the people in the cellar?

359
00:38:24,360 --> 00:38:26,240
Who are they?

360
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:31,200
Mommy and Daddy looked a long time
to find the perfect boy child.

361
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:34,880
But each one they found turned out bad.

362
00:38:35,480 --> 00:38:37,520
Some saw things
they weren't supposed to.

363
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:40,520
Others heard too much,
others talked back.

364
00:38:42,360 --> 00:38:46,560
Daddy cut out the bad parts
and put the boys in the cellar,...

365
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:48,840
..one by one.

366
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:51,760
When they get flashlights
and food of some kind,...

367
00:38:52,080 --> 00:38:54,240
..they're happy in their own way.

368
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:57,640
Yeah, right.

369
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:04,640
What about you?

370
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:08,160
How come they haven't
put you in the cellar?

371
00:39:09,280 --> 00:39:13,800
I do not see, or hear, or speak evil.

372
00:39:20,120 --> 00:39:22,200
It's the only way.

373
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:31,320
- What is that?
- What?

374
00:39:31,680 --> 00:39:34,320
- That yellin'. What is that?
- Well, that's Roach.

375
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:36,120
- Roach?
- That's who Daddy's hunting.

376
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:40,840
See, Daddy hates Roach cos he got
out of the cellar and into the walls.

377
00:39:41,440 --> 00:39:42,600
And Daddy can't find him.

378
00:39:58,240 --> 00:40:02,480
- There must be another way out.
- Further into the house. Here.

379
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:06,000
Father's too big to follow,
and he's afraid of what's in there.

380
00:40:06,560 --> 00:40:09,720
- I don't want in, I want out.
- Sometimes in is out.

381
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:18,000
Forget it.

382
00:40:26,440 --> 00:40:28,720
I hear ya! I hear ya!

383
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:34,960
Yes.

384
00:40:35,480 --> 00:40:37,720
- OK, I'll get in there.

385
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:05,360
I'm gonna get ya!

386
00:41:06,280 --> 00:41:07,560
- Yes!

387
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:16,400
I've got something for my Princey. Yes!

388
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:18,920
Come on. Come on. Come on.

389
00:41:20,640 --> 00:41:22,360
Good appetite.

390
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:25,840
Healthy Prince... a secure home.

391
00:41:31,120 --> 00:41:32,880
Stay.

392
00:41:34,560 --> 00:41:38,880
The vehicle registration matches
that of a van used in a 211 last night.

393
00:41:47,920 --> 00:41:50,000
Daddy. Police out back.

394
00:41:55,080 --> 00:41:55,800
Damn.

395
00:42:12,400 --> 00:42:14,480
Hey, police! Police!

396
00:42:18,760 --> 00:42:21,280
Police! Police!

397
00:42:22,720 --> 00:42:25,480
Hello. What can I do for you, gentlemen?

398
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:27,800
- Good afternoon, ma'am.
- Is this your van?

399
00:42:28,480 --> 00:42:32,080
Goodness, no. It was just standing here
when we got back from shopping.

400
00:42:32,320 --> 00:42:35,000
- Did you see anybody around?
- Trouble?

401
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:38,320
Well, as a matter of fact
we did see a couple of men -

402
00:42:38,560 --> 00:42:40,280
one black, one white -

403
00:42:40,960 --> 00:42:42,840
walking away as we approached.

404
00:42:42,880 --> 00:42:45,120
We thought they were
service people of some sort.

405
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:48,040
- They were working on your door.
- No harm done.

406
00:42:48,720 --> 00:42:50,800
- We'll check the house.
- Just checked it.

407
00:42:51,120 --> 00:42:53,640
Even looked under the beds.
Clean as a whistle.

408
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:56,040
Well, let's recon the neighborhood.

409
00:42:56,400 --> 00:42:59,360
- Do you get a lot of this?
- It's as if we're the prisoners,...

410
00:43:00,080 --> 00:43:02,480
-.. and the criminals roam free.
- I know what you mean.

411
00:43:02,920 --> 00:43:06,480
You're lucky. This van was used
in a liquor-store robbery last night.

412
00:43:07,200 --> 00:43:09,680
- Oh, goodness.
- Liquor store?

413
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:13,160
I'd advise you to stay inside,
keep your doors locked for a while.

414
00:43:13,760 --> 00:43:15,880
You can count on it.

415
00:43:20,880 --> 00:43:22,840
Hope you catch 'em.

416
00:43:24,280 --> 00:43:27,040
- Catch 'em in hell.
- Oh, my God.

417
00:43:28,480 --> 00:43:31,000
- What?
- There's not just the two.

418
00:43:35,240 --> 00:43:37,360
There's a boy.

419
00:43:37,760 --> 00:43:39,880
He's in there right now...

420
00:43:41,440 --> 00:43:43,280
..with our little angel!

421
00:44:14,120 --> 00:44:15,800
God! What are they feedin' you?

422
00:44:32,040 --> 00:44:34,080
What is it, boy?

423
00:44:55,160 --> 00:44:57,600
You come in here
and I'm gonna kick your ass!

424
00:45:18,760 --> 00:45:20,200
Gonna kill you!

425
00:45:26,720 --> 00:45:28,480
Kill.

426
00:45:30,240 --> 00:45:31,960
Kill them!

427
00:45:54,960 --> 00:45:56,680
Is this your place?

428
00:46:06,880 --> 00:46:10,240
- What hit you?
- The damn Bear Trooper.

429
00:46:10,760 --> 00:46:14,080
But Prince is after him.
He'll kill him before he gets to Alice.

430
00:46:23,240 --> 00:46:24,800
Let's do somethin'!

431
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:38,840
Do you hear something?

432
00:46:48,800 --> 00:46:50,960
The boy's gotten to Alice.

433
00:47:09,440 --> 00:47:10,960
Thanks.

434
00:47:14,440 --> 00:47:16,960
He doesn't talk much, does he?

435
00:47:17,600 --> 00:47:19,840
His... his tongue's cut out.

436
00:47:23,640 --> 00:47:25,280
Oh, man!

437
00:47:25,560 --> 00:47:28,720
My mother caught him trying to
call for help one day, and...

438
00:47:29,080 --> 00:47:32,240
-.. Daddy had to teach him...
- Speak no evil, right?

439
00:47:34,520 --> 00:47:37,520
Your father's one sick mother,
you know that?

440
00:47:37,880 --> 00:47:40,640
Actually, your mother's
one sick mother, too.

441
00:47:41,240 --> 00:47:42,760
Sh!

442
00:47:42,680 --> 00:47:46,800
You're speaking evil. They'd kill you
if they heard a word you just said.

443
00:47:50,560 --> 00:47:52,920
Roach. Roach is my friend.

444
00:47:53,320 --> 00:47:55,000
Roach?

445
00:47:56,160 --> 00:47:59,280
I'm Poindexter. Everybody calls me Fool.

446
00:48:00,520 --> 00:48:02,000
Fool?

447
00:48:03,760 --> 00:48:05,840
We sure got the names, huh?

448
00:48:13,440 --> 00:48:15,360
Is this Leroy?

449
00:48:19,640 --> 00:48:22,680
You did this? Why do you make these?

450
00:48:24,160 --> 00:48:26,880
To hold the souls
of burglars when they died.

451
00:48:27,520 --> 00:48:31,040
Or salesmen, workmen...
other people who saw too much.

452
00:48:43,880 --> 00:48:45,800
There she is!

453
00:48:49,040 --> 00:48:50,880
You viper in my bosom!

454
00:48:50,960 --> 00:48:53,840
- You little Judas!
- What do I do with him, Mommy?

455
00:48:54,640 --> 00:48:56,960
It is time to clean house!

456
00:49:00,720 --> 00:49:03,480
Total spring-cleaning.

457
00:49:04,560 --> 00:49:07,760
OK, let's move it!
Pull, you little piece of shit!

458
00:49:09,880 --> 00:49:11,960
No, wait a minute!

459
00:49:25,160 --> 00:49:30,120
I am sick and tired of your attitude!
You will do your chore now!

460
00:49:33,480 --> 00:49:35,560
Clean it up, for God's sake!

461
00:49:36,840 --> 00:49:38,480
What is a mother to do?

462
00:49:38,760 --> 00:49:42,320
Lazy brat sits in her room
all day, sewing dolls!

463
00:49:44,040 --> 00:49:46,360
Children misbehaving in the basement!

464
00:49:47,400 --> 00:49:49,440
And one in the walls,...

465
00:49:49,800 --> 00:49:52,600
..doing his business God knows where!

466
00:49:54,120 --> 00:49:56,360
You kids'll be the death of me!

467
00:49:58,920 --> 00:50:00,560
The death of me.

468
00:50:28,880 --> 00:50:30,960
I keep 'em real hungry.

469
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:36,320
I ask a simple thing -

470
00:50:36,640 --> 00:50:41,440
just clean up that awful man's blood -
and what do you do?

471
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:46,480
You get it all over your nice,
clean dress I worked so hard to make!

472
00:50:47,200 --> 00:50:49,640
Now get in that tub and scrub yourself!

473
00:50:50,080 --> 00:50:51,800
No!

474
00:50:52,000 --> 00:50:54,360
Don't wanna get in, huh?
Well, let me help you!

475
00:50:57,280 --> 00:50:59,400
You scrub yourself!

476
00:51:00,640 --> 00:51:03,120
You scrub yourself! It's hot!

477
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:05,640
The fires of hell are hotter!

478
00:51:23,440 --> 00:51:25,400
No! Don't put me in there!

479
00:51:25,840 --> 00:51:27,800
No! No!

480
00:51:35,440 --> 00:51:37,160
No!

481
00:51:41,440 --> 00:51:43,520
Where's the Bear Trooper?

482
00:51:47,840 --> 00:51:49,560
Dead meat.

483
00:51:51,480 --> 00:51:55,120
I could've killed him, but I let
the people under the stairs do it.

484
00:52:15,120 --> 00:52:16,560
Leave me alone!

485
00:52:18,400 --> 00:52:20,560
Get away from me!

486
00:52:42,640 --> 00:52:44,400
Roach.

487
00:52:47,040 --> 00:52:48,920
It's right there, Roach.

488
00:52:53,880 --> 00:52:56,680
